“It is a good win for us because we continue to keep teams at the top of the league on toes. My players followed my instructions and that is what aided us to score and contain our opponents,” Ayany told Nation Sport.At Bukhungu stadium in Kakamega, MCF shocked host Soy United at home as Kelvin Ochieng’s 52nd minute strike decided the tough tie between the two teams. Talanta FC on Wednesday cut Police FC's lead at the summit of the National Super League (NSL) to two points after hitting bottom placed Mount Kenya 3-0 at Camp Toyoyo grounds in Nairobi. 

Strikers Francis Kairo and Ken Mutembei scored a goal each in the first half before Barrack Odhiambo added the third in the second half to give Talanta their ninth win of the season. 



